\n<p><img src=\"https://imgur.com/1h9o2Kx.png\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">No Enchantment Cap Level removes the limit from the enchantment level put it from Minecraft devs, now the limit 255 was increase to&nbsp;2147483647 (Integer limit) , also you can put negative levels like -1, -100, -10000000. Now you can put any enchant in any item with the new command /setenchant, check the wiki and learn how to used</span></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://imgur.com/xAPPVoI.gif\" width=\"413\" height=\"233\" />&nbsp;<img src=\"https://imgur.com/eIRCTYW.gif\" width=\"413\" height=\"233\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://imgur.com/1h9o2Kx.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"838\" height=\"34\" /></p>\n<p><em><strong>F.A.Q.s</strong></em><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Q: Can I include No Enchantments Cap Level in my mod pack?</strong><br />A: Sure, just put my mod in the related projects</span></p>\n<p><strong>Q: The /setenchant command works in non op players?</strong><br />A: No, you need to have operator to use the command</p>",
